The paper deals with compressed sensing matrices and their construction, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) categories. The use of BCH codes and FFT algorithms suggests a connection to Coding Theory (cs.CC) and Data Structures (cs.DS). Finally, the application of simple greedy algorithms and coherence-based RIP analysis points towards Machine Learning (cs.LG).
